First, make sure you have Node.js installed on your system. Then, follow these steps to create a Discord bot using Discord.js v14 and a single command, ban:

1. Install Discord.js by running the following command:
```bash
npm install discord.js
```
1. Create a new JavaScript file, e.g., `bot.js`, and add the following code:
```javascript
const { Client, Intents } = require('discord.js');
const PREFIX = '!';

const client = new Client({ intents: [Intents.GUILDS, Intents.GUILD_MEMBERS, Intents.GUILD_BANS] });

client.on('ready', () => {
    console.log(`Bot is online!`);
});

client.on('message', async (message) => {
    if (message.author.bot) return;

    const args = message.content.slice(PREFIX.length).trim().split(/ +/);
    const command = args.shift().toLowerCase();

    if (command === 'ban') {
        if (!message.guild) return message.reply('This command is only available in servers.');

        const member = message.guild.members.fetch(args[0]);
        if (!member) return message.reply('Member not found.');

        try {
            await member.ban();
            message.reply('Member banned successfully.');
        } catch (error) {
            message.reply('Failed to ban member.');
        }
    }
});

client.login('YOUR_BOT_TOKEN_HERE');
```
Replace `'YOUR_BOT_TOKEN_HERE'` with your bot's token. You can obtain this from the Discord Developer Portal: <https://discord.com/developers/applications>

1. Save the file and run the bot:
```bash
node bot.js
```
Now, you should see the bot online and ready to receive commands in the Discord Developer Portal. To test the bot, join a server with the bot and send a message containing the slash command `!ban @member` (replace `@member` with the user's Discord username). The bot should ban the specified user.

